 the cardiovascular safety of e‐cigarettes.<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.ahajournals.org/doi/10.1161/JAHA.117.006353\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ahajournals.org%2Fdoi%2F10.1161%2FJAHA.117.006353&d=tLsEO8KpRnvfRHW%2FlT3TjjUVmWcutTvqHtF1LT7nQkc%3D&h=5ea0c8b5\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.ahajournals.org/doi/10.1161/JAHA.117.006353</a> <br />\n有權威既美國journal，有table list哂你可能吸入既物質<br />\n<br />\nThe long‐term health effects of e‐cigarettes have not yet been documented in humans; however, the short‐term negative effects have been suggested by several studies.8, 9, 26, 27 These studies focused mainly on the cytotoxic profile of e‐cigarettes and their effects on the respiratory tract,9, 26, 27 central nervous system,9, 10 immune system28, 29 and a few others9, 30, 31 (Table 1).<br />\n<br />\n入面已經講e cig就算冇長期研究，不過短期負效果已經well established，包括肺炎，致癌，影響免疫系統<br />\n<br />\nEpidemiological and clinical studies suggest a strong association between human exposure to PM2.5 and the risk of cardiovascular disease development. Specifically, these studies showed that exposure to PM2.5 from ambient air pollution and/or tobacco smoking is linked to hypertension,156 coronary artery disease,157 myocardial infarction,158, 159 atherosclerosis,156 arrhythmia160 as well as mortality relative risk.161, 162<br />\n<br />\n樓主最關心既心血管病，篇野都講e cig既煙產生PM2.5對心血管好有影響，會導致高血壓，心肌梗塞，血管栓塞，心律不正，從而提高死亡率<br />\n<br />\n其實要做research不如信下有well controlled study同有權威既"},{"pid":"cc2be0793b48236fb91e03bca0096a7d1102cd34","tid":1126835,"uid":101823,"like":1,"dislike":0,"score":1,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-04-26T18:47:42.000Z","msg":"你一係繼續食一係戒架姐<br />\n有咩好講"},{"pid":"f48f23f7da486257ad203291b27df5d8384b5ab0","tid":1126835,"uid":17232,"like":5,"dislike":1,"score":4,"quote":{"pid":"ee63b9123d2704bbf950c8828bd0ddb2043da48a","tid":1126835,"uid":222475,"like":108,"dislike":2,"score":106,"quote":{"pid":"c9a3ce1d7ac7ecc1b26df40f656cd57f486b129c","tid":1126835,"uid":244387,