害減少95%：<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/news/e-cigarettes-around-95-less-harmful-than-tobacco-estimates-landmark-review\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.uk%2Fgovernment%2Fnews%2Fe-cigarettes-around-95-less-harmful-than-tobacco-estimates-landmark-review&d=tLsEO8KpRnvfRHW%2FlT3TjjUVmWcutTvqHtF1LT7nQkc%3D&h=8056f534\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.gov.uk/government/news/e-cigarettes-around-95-less-harmful-than-tobacco-estimates-landmark-review</a><br />\n個網都不停鼓勵吸煙人士轉食電子煙：<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/health-and-social-care/smoking\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.gov.uk%2Fhealth-and-social-care%2Fsmoking&d=tLsEO8KpRnvfRHW%2FlT3TjjUVmWcutTvqHtF1LT7nQkc%3D&h=4b07c031\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://www.gov.uk/health-and-social-care/smoking</a>"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2019-04-26T19:10:51.000Z","msg":"個網冇講過e cigarettes係傳統煙既substitution, 美國FDA都唔鼓勵用vaping戒煙, 都冇話佢係安全<br />\n<br />\nThe Food and Drug Administration has not found any e-cigarette to be safe and effective in helping smokers quit."},"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-04-26T20:50:58.000Z","msg":"Sorry, 我之前睇過好多有關vaping既資料, <a href=\"http://我只記得係喺gov.uk\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=http%3A%2F%2F%E6%88%91%E5%8F%AA%E8%A8%98%E5%BE%97%E4%BF%82%E5%96%BAgov.uk&d=tLsEO8KpRnvfRHW%2FlT3TjjUVmWcutTvqHtF1LT7nQkc%3D&h=b37352f7\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">我只記得係喺gov.uk</a>度睇到英國政府encourage smoker to switch我先會買黎試, 但我無save低exactly個post.<br />\n不過我搵到個類似既, 師兄可以睇下, 呢份野係Public Health England (PHE) 既一個叫Martin Dockrell (Tobacco Control Programme Lead)寫: <a href=\"https://publichealthmatters.blog.gov.uk/2019/02/27/e-cigarette-evidence-update-patterns-and-use-in-adults-and-young-people/\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fpublichealthmatters.blog.gov.uk%2F2019%2F02%2F27%2Fe-cigarette-evidence-update-patterns-and-use-in-adults-and-young-people%2F&d=tLsEO8KpRnvfRHW%2FlT3TjjUVmWcutTvqHtF1LT7nQkc%3D&h=df8f4f4b\" data-auto-link target=\"_blank\">https://publichealthmatters.blog.gov.uk/2019/02/27/e-cigarette-evidence-update-patterns-and-use-in-adults-and-young-people/</a><br />\n<br />\nIn brief, they are not completely risk free, but vaping is far less harmful than smoking &ndash; a view supported by many including the Royal College of Physicians, Cancer Research UK and the US National Academy of Sciences. Growing evidence also suggests that using an e-cigarette can be one of the most effective ways to quit.<br />\nOur report recommends that Stop Smoking Services should do more to encourage smokers that want to quit with the help of an e-cigarette. All services, and indeed other healthcare professionals, should encourage smokers who want to quit by switching to vaping.<br />\nFor the public, our advice remains the same: if you&rsquo;re not a smoker, don&rsquo;t start and don&rsquo;t vape. If you&rsquo;re a smoker, quit now and consider using an e-cigarette to help you. Remember that using a quit aid along with support from your local stop smoking service gives you the best chance of quitting successfully.<br />\n<br />\n當然啦, 我都唔認為vaping就對大家無害, 亦都可以好肯定咁講, 有決心戒煙既人一日就戒甩, 大部分煙民都唔係因為尼古丁上癮而要食煙, 而係&quot;想食&quot;搞到上癮<br />\n點都好, 我唔係科學家, 唔識點test vaping對身體有無害, 但假如電子煙/加熱煙係真係減少對煙民身體既傷害 (我唔係講緊要佢地成功quit smoking), 點解政府唔可以立法管制埋電子煙<br />\n至於要減低對其他人既影響應該要由管理可吸煙範圍入手, 而家唔比喺公共場所食煙已經可以減少對非煙民既傷害 (我都好憎比人噴煙/火車頭)"},{"pid":"df9569c29743305da72c89dd82859081f1650f2b","tid":1126835,"uid":73729,"like":0,"dislike":0,"score":0,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2019-04-26T21:55:26.000Z","msg":"<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/bomb.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"}]}